# BizPresence Pro — Cursor Rules

## Project purpose

Config-driven **corporate website template**. Replace the **`company`** block in `site.config.ts` for each deployment. Do not hardcode organization-specific copy in components.

## Stack

- Next.js 16 (App Router, static export)
- TypeScript 5, Tailwind CSS v4, Lucide React
- Jest + React Testing Library

## Content

- Source of truth: **`src/config/site.config.ts`**
- Components import `siteConfig` from `@/config/site.config`
- Metadata in `src/app/*/page.tsx` should use `siteConfig.company` where appropriate

## Styling

Prefer utilities from **`src/app/globals.css`**: `.card`, `.badge`, `.btn-primary`, `.btn-ghost`, `.gradient-text`, `.surface`, `.stat-card`, `.client-tile`, `.hero-section`, etc. Theme is warm white + orange accents.

## Structure

- `src/app/` — routes and thin page wrappers
- `src/components/sections/` — one file per major section
- `src/components/ui/` — shared primitives (e.g. `ChatWidget`, `LogoIcon`)
- `src/lib/` — `assetPath`, `chatbotReply`, etc.

## Testing

- Use `data-testid` for stable selectors
- Run `npm test` and `npm run lint` before commits

## Deployment

- Static output: `out/` after `npm run build`
- Subpath hosting: set `NEXT_PUBLIC_BASE_PATH`; use `assetPath()` for public images when needed
